text: Seventy-six years ago today, fear, hate, and division led to the signing of Executive Order 9066 – the order for Japanese Internment. We cannot repeat these mistakes. #DayOfRemembrance
Sending warm wishes to everyone welcoming the Lunar New Year. May it be a happy and healthy one.

Approximately 19,000 Dreamers have lost DACA status since Trump created this crisis. That’s 19,000 young people who must live in fear of deportation. After March 5, that number explodes – increasing by about 1,000 per day. Congress must act to protect them.

This week, we celebrate a great American hero – Frederick Douglass. Born into slavery, he chose yesterday – February 14 – as his birthday. Two-hundred years later, we remember his conviction and struggle, and we recommit ourselves. There’s progress that’s yet to be made.
Another moment of silence won't suffice. This country is weary of tragedy. Congress must act to address gun violence.
One of my most joyous memories is of Valentine’s Day in 2004. I’d just been elected District Attorney of San Francisco. I was on my way to SFO, and I decided to stop at City Hall.

I meet Dreamers every week. They are here walking the halls of Congress all the time. They scrape together enough for travel, take time off their jobs, and find places to stay – all because they feel like they have to be here so we see them. Their futures are in our hands.

This year’s U.S. Winter Olympic Team is a reminder that our country’s strength comes from its diversity. I’m especially proud of the 22 Californians representing us this year. Good luck @TeamUSA. I can't wait to watch you bring home the gold!

It’s a false choice to say we can’t fund the government, protect Dreamers, and reauthorize CHIP. We can and should do all three. What’s preventing us from a bipartisan agreement is the White House.

How do Americans feel about the tax bill Republicans passed yesterday? I’ll let the numbers speak for themselves.

Since the tax bill was introduced, I’ve gotten 122,981 letters about it:

97.6% opposed it

2.4% supported it
